🌿 ब्रह्मगीता – ऐन्दवोपाख्यानम् (सर्ग १७८)
भाग १० : सम्पूर्ण जगत चिन्मात्र है
Brahma Gītā – Aindava Upākhyāna (Sarga 178)
Final Part: The Entire Universe Is Pure Consciousness
मूल श्लोक
चिन्मात्रखकुलालेन स्वदेहचलचक्रके।
स्वशरीरमृदा सर्गः कुतोऽयं क्रियतेऽनिशम्॥४९॥
संकल्पनिर्मिते सर्गे दृशदश्चेन्न चेतनाः।
तदत्र लोष्टशैलादि किमेतदिति कथ्यताम्॥५०॥
कलनस्मृतिसंस्काराः दधत्यर्थं च नोदरे।
प्राङ्मृष्टं कल्पनादीनामन्यैवार्थकलावताम्॥५१॥

🌿 हिन्दी भावार्थ
अब श्रीवसिष्ठजी सम्पूर्ण उपदेश का अंतिम निष्कर्ष प्रस्तुत करते हैं।
वे एक अद्भुत उपमा देते हैं।
यदि कोई कहे कि यह सम्पूर्ण सृष्टि ब्रह्म द्वारा रची जाती है,
तो प्रश्न उठता है—
किस पदार्थ से?
यदि कुम्हार मिट्टी से घड़ा बनाता है,
तो ब्रह्म किस मिट्टी से जगत बनाता है?
क्या ब्रह्म के अतिरिक्त कोई दूसरी वस्तु है?
नहीं।
इसलिए यह कल्पना ही असम्भव है कि ब्रह्म किसी बाहरी पदार्थ से जगत का निर्माण करता है।
यदि सब कुछ चैतन्य से प्रकट है,
तो पत्थर,
मिट्टी,
पर्वत,
वृक्ष,
और शरीर—
इन सबको अचेतन कैसे कहा जा सकता है?
अचेतन का अस्तित्व स्वयं सिद्ध नहीं है।
जो कुछ भी जाना जाता है,
वह केवल चेतना में ही जाना जाता है।
अनुभव,
स्मृति,
संस्कार,
इच्छा,
ज्ञान—
ये सब चेतना के ही प्रकाश में सम्भव हैं।
इसलिए वस्तुओं की सत्ता भी चेतना से पृथक् नहीं है।
जैसे तरंग जल से भिन्न नहीं,
वैसे ही जगत ब्रह्म से भिन्न नहीं।

🌿 English Reflection
Sage Vasiṣṭha now brings the entire dialogue to its magnificent conclusion.
He asks a simple yet devastating question.
If Brahman creates the universe,
what material does Brahman use?
A potter requires clay.
A carpenter requires wood.
A sculptor requires stone.
But what exists apart from Brahman
that could become the universe?
Nothing.
Therefore creation cannot be understood as one object producing another.
The universe is not fashioned from a second substance.
It is simply Consciousness appearing as names and forms.
Vasiṣṭha then turns to Sri Rama's original doubt.
"If stones in the imagined universe are not Consciousness,
then what exactly are the stones in this universe?"
Everything that is ever experienced
is experienced only in Consciousness.
Memory,
perception,
knowledge,
thought,
and every object of experience
shine only because Consciousness illumines them.
Nothing possesses an existence independent of that Light.

🌿 Vedantic Insight
This is the final resolution of the entire Sarga.
Sri Rama began by asking:
"How does the formless move the formed?"
Sri Vasiṣṭha answers:
It never does.
Because the "formed"
has never existed independently of the Formless.
The wave never leaves the ocean.
The ornament never leaves the gold.
The dream never leaves the mind.
Likewise,
the universe never departs from Pure Consciousness.
Advaita is therefore not the union of two realities.
It is the recognition that there has always been only One.

🌿 Practical Contemplation
Look around you.
The chair.
The tree.
The mountain.
The sky.
Your own body.
Instead of asking,
"What are these made of?"
Ask,
"Without Awareness, could any of these ever be known?"
The answer quietly reveals itself.
Everything is known in Consciousness.
Everything shines because of Consciousness.
Everything returns to Consciousness.

🌸 Grand Conclusion of Sarga 178
Maharshi Vasiṣṭha has now dissolved the deepest philosophical problem.
The question was never,
"How does Consciousness contact matter?"
The real discovery is:
Matter has never stood apart from Consciousness.
There has never been a second substance.
There has never been an independent universe.
There has never been anything outside Brahman.
The seeker who realizes this no longer searches for God as another.
He awakens to the timeless Truth:
The Seer,
the Seeing,
and the Seen
are one indivisible Consciousness.
अहं ब्रह्मास्मि।
सर्वं खल्विदं ब्रह्म।
तत्त्वमसि।
These are not three different teachings.
They are one realization,
seen from three different standpoints.
